..::About Drugs Inc::..
How does the drug trade work? Can it be stopped or should it be regulated? And what are the personal costs?
Those are just some of the questions answered in this miniseries, a comprehensive look at society's most abused drugs: cocaine, methamphetamine, heroin and marijuana.
First-person perspectives from traffickers, dealers, users, law enforcement and
medical professionals detail how the drugs are processed and moved onto the streets, and the effects they have on the human body
